Package: cic
Title: Changes-in-Changes Estimator with Asymptotic Confidence
        Intervals
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Timothée", "Bacchi", email = "timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Timothée Bacchi
Maintainer: Timothée Bacchi <timothee.bacchi@etu.minesparis.psl.eu>
Description: Implements the Changes-in-Changes estimator (Athey & Imbens, 2006)
    defined as the average of the quantile-transformed ranks. Provides
    asymptotic confidence intervals via a full-sample (no-split) variance estimator and bootstrap alternatives (percentile and
    standard-error). The core computations are written in C++ via Rcpp for
    performance. Includes a comprehensive diagnostic tool, check_cic_assumptions(),
    that validates empirical data against theoretical assumptions (sampling balance,
    continuity, tail behavior, and convergence rates). Features robust input
    validation, graceful error handling for missing compiled code, and pure R
    fallback implementations for maximum compatibility.
